
This is the pubcookie relay.  

Build: e.g. 
 
  (build the pubcookie login server first)
  (then, e.g.)

  $ ./configure --prefix=/usr/local/apache/htodcs/PCRELAY \
               --with-pubcookie=.. \
               --with-webtpl=/usr/local/webtpl
  $ make
  $ make install

(For the webtpl library, see:  http://staff.washington.edu/fox/webtpl)


Use;


  Configure your remote applications to use the relay uri as a login server.

  Pubcookie (/usr/local/pubcookie/config) variables:

    login_uri:  <uri of the real login server>
    login_host: <host of the real login server>

    relay_template_path: <path th your relay's template directory>
                          -- usually: (prefix)/templates --
    relay_uri:  <uri of your relay>





